Implement rename and relink commands.

`chipper mv <id> <new-filename>`:
  Rename a ticket file on disk and update chipper-slugs to point to the new filename.

`chipper relink <id> <filename>`:
  Link an orphaned slug to an existing file on disk.
  Preserves the slug, priority index, and status of the orphaned entry.
  Used when a file was renamed manually outside of chipper.

`chipper slug <id> <new-slug>`:
  Rename a ticket's slug in both chipper-slugs and chipper-queue.
  Reject if the new slug is already taken.

When unregistered files are detected alongside orphaned entries, chipper may
suggest relinking them interactively (see list-commands and orphaned behavior).

Depends on: cli-scaffolding, manifest-implementation
